Abstract

Internationalized Domain Name (IDN) makes expression of domain name rich. The demand for such enrichment is to use native language characters in a domain name. IDN itself has no language dependency as a protocol, but to utilize IDN in the real world, language and/or regional aspects should be taken into account.

This document defines Japanese character variant table for .JP registry.

Also, this document explains a guideline to any DNS zone administrator who accepts Japanese as an IDN label.
